The real breakthrough is not the tutoring.

It is that the notebook stores transformations, not just results.

So every page becomes:

State₀ → State₁ → State₂ → State₃

A structured reasoning chain.

That aligns almost perfectly with your earlier idea:

meaning exists in the difference between states.

This notebook literally records the differences between states of thought.

Which makes it a meaning engine for mathematics.

